The district unit of the Telugu Desam Party urged the Union Government to confer Bharat Ratna on TDP founder-president N.T. Rama Rao.Participating in a programme to mark the 20th death anniversary of Mr. Rama Rao, after garlanding his statue on the outskirts of Karimnagar town on Monday, party district president Ch Vijayaramana Rao said he deserves the honour for his service to mankind.Welfare schemesHe recollected several welfare schemes launched by Mr. Rama Rao - such as Rs.2-a-kg rice, saree and dhoti scheme, political empowerment of the weaker sections and others.Party leaders Ganta Ramulu Goud, Kalledapu Agaiah, Putta Narender, and others paid floral tributes to NTR. On the occasion, about 30 Telugunadu Studentâ€™s Federation activists donated blood at government headquarters hospital.